decrementReferralCredits(address,uint256.details: Decrements referral credits for a given referrer.

params.artistCredits: Number of artist credits to remove.
params.organizerCredits: Number of organizer credits to remove.
params.referrer: The address of the referrer whose credits are to be decremented.
params.venueCredits: Number of venue credits to remove.

getReferralCredits(address).details: Retrieves the referral credits for a specified address.

params.referrer: The address to retrieve referral credits for.

returns._0: The referral credits of the specified address.

incrementReferralCredits(address,uint256.details: Increments referral credits for a given referrer.

params.artistCredits: Number of artist credits to add.
params.organizerCredits: Number of organizer credits to add.
params.referrer: The address of the referrer whose credits are to be incremented.
params.venueCredits: Number of venue credits to add.

initialize(address).details: Initializes the contract by setting the initial owner and preparing it for upgradeability.

params.initialOwner: Address to be set as the initial owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setCreditControlPermission(address,bool).details: Sets or revokes permission for an address to decrement referral credits.

params.contractAddress: The address to update permission for.
params.permission: True to allow, false to revoke.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.
